[03:44] <timo> since <( is a zero-width atom, it doesn't mean very much

[03:44] <timo> it will match a literal `{}` and put the start of the match in between

[03:45] <timo> and if there's no } directly after the { it will fail the match

[03:45] <grondilu> well that's LTA IMHO

[03:45] <timo> do you have a proposal to make it better?

